html: Devastated by the loss of her closest companion, a former bodyguard embarks on a mission to honor her beloved friend's final desire: a bittersweet quest for vengeance. Consumed by sorrow, she is determined to avenge her friend's tragic fate, unleashing a relentless pursuit for justice that knows no bounds. With the weight of sorrow propelling her forward, she sets out on a path of retribution, where her skills and determination will be put to the ultimate test. No longer bound by the constraints of her former profession, she becomes a force to be reckoned with, channeling her grief into an unstoppable force that will forever alter the course of those responsible. As she dives deeper into the heart of darkness, the ex-bodyguard risks everything to bring closure to her friend's memory, leaving no stone unturned and no wrong unpunished.

html: <script type="text/json" class="contextData">{"globals":{"UNSUPPORTED":false,"DOMAIN_NAME":"about.me","DOMAIN_NAME_URL":"https://about.me","DATA_WAREHOUSE_API":"https://dw.about.me","NODE_API":"https://api.about.me","IMGIX_URL":"aboutme.imgix.net","ENVIRONMENT":"production","AUTH_TOKEN":"3192597759990468663951221567294","funnels":{"20190116_homepage":{"choice":"control"},"20210903_no_email_signup":{"choice":"experiment"},"20230206_less_branding":{"choice":"control"}},"SLACK":{},"USER_AGENT":"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64; rv:121.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/121.0","NODE_ENV":"production","CONFIG":{"google.recaptcha.key":"6LeywBMUAAAAAGfSJKikt0fFaGKvImrnvwNte3Ez","google.recaptcha.v3.key":"6Le9Ny4aAAAAAF426psvaMHCrsAkf2jAaI4LIUCu","google.recaptcha.url":"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js","hcaptcha.sitekey":"802c469f-ed34-47f3-aae6-8cb966cc1798","onboarding.captcha.enabled":true,"pumpkinhead.globals.aws_images":"assets.about.me","pumpkinhead.globals.domain_mapping_proxy_ips":["52.2.64.1"],"pumpkinhead.globals.facebook_app_id":249413078192,"social.google.client_id":"828605907544-2lag7tdq7k3ebk4pvjiu45vdpggiu2k0.apps.googleusercontent.com","pumpkinhead.globals.js_debug":false,"pumpkinhead.globals.store_key":"pk_live_RlI4aulcrfnDp0vi1aZHyc8y","pumpkinhead.googleplaces.key":"AIzaSyCXfGyejICxDjkGahy3CBbSZ8_43lWwP9w","sentry.dsn.browser.client":"https://4e376b84dfa54d438285936f87ce3cfe@o477720.ingest.sentry.io/5525987","user_files.allowed_extensions":["pdf"],"image_processor_url":"https://images.about.me","pumpkinhead.globals.aws_images_bucket":"assets.about.me"}},"page":{"id":"profile","user":{"flags":{"has_password":false,"admin":false,"premium":true},"user_id":5013991,"user_name":"marucolbert","first_name":"Maru","last_name":"Colbert","bio":"<p>Hello! I’m Maru, a professor in the sciences and practitioner of the arts. My teaching and research areas are phytoremediation, micro-scale processes, climate science/ atmospheric modeling, surface chemistry, NOx sensing and pre-engineering education. I combined these topics in postdoctoral and international field studies. I teach and lead research teams at universities in the US and abroad (Australia, Canada, the UK, China and Africa).</p><p>My STEAM work stems from my profession and passion-providing resources to counter the lack of proficiency in STEM subjects due to inequity in education. My STE(A)M initiatives are in 4 cities in the U.S. and 3 countries in Africa.</p><p>Hobbies I enjoy include volleyball, skating, sewing, running, reading and performing. Additionally, I practice innovative design.</p><p>PLEASE GO TO MAPOETRY.ORG-THE ONLINE GALLERY, TO VIEW OR PURCHASE ONE OF MY TWO WINNING EKPHRASTIC ART/POETRY PIECES.</p><p>Another poem is featured at https://masspoetry.org/61621-harris-colbert</p><p>Each month I work on one (or more) of these charitable, social or civic initiatives.</p><p>This year's list includes The Boutique 4 Good; The Innocent Convicts; Liberia Labs-Teaching &amp; Research Project; Oxfemwa; The NAACP; Annie Cannons-MIT Solve; BAMIT; Minds Matter Boston; Maranyundo Girls School (Rwanda); NSBE-Region I-Boston [including Ghana]; The Empowerment Series/Social Justice Circle for Engaged Activism; (Charity Marathons) Leukemia &amp; Lymphoma Society, American Cancer Society/Dana Farber, American Heart Association, American Diabetes Association and The March of Dimes; Her'tazhe Productions, MASS Poetry and True Story Theater.</p><p>I give back as I move forward since I realize...it's a blessing to BE.</p><p>During the Fall of 2020 I was a participant in the TC2 PlayLab's (virtual) Fall Showcase. To view the entire show's social justice selections, click on the YouTube shown below. To see the monologue I performed, featuring a grandmother to granddaughter Facetime session, use the link below (40:38-47:00) at https://www. youtube.com/watch?v=Vb4UULs HuDM&amp;feature=youtube. My recitation was done near Thanksgiving 2020, when relatives were \"Zooming\"/\"Facetiming\" instead of being together.</p><p>Click on the \"+\" above, for my short \"life blasts\"!</p><p>December…most importantly, my birth month…and everlastingly, for me, the month the savior was born. “..We clap hands and welcome the peace of Christmas. We beckon this good season to wait a while with us..\" Maya Angelou (Amazing Peace)</p><p>BE WELL, STAY SAFE!</p>","contact_me":{"enabled":true,"display":"button"},"tags":[],"interests":[{"interest":"Volleyball"},{"interest":"Running"},{"interest":"Dance"},{"interest":"Music"},{"interest":"Innovation"}],"locations":[{"components":[{"short_name":"MA","long_name":"Massachusetts","types":["administrative_area_level_1","political"]},{"short_name":"US","long_name":"United States","types":["country","political"]}],"source":"google","location":"Massachusetts, United States"}],"schools":[],"jobs":[],"roles":[{"role":"Professor"},{"role":"Director"},{"role":"Designer"}],"video":{"type":"youtube","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vb4UULsHuDM&t=2506s","video_id":"Vb4UULsHuDM","video_thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vb4UULsHuDM/maxresdefault.jpg"},"testimonials":{"header":"0","items":[{"quote":"I knew Professor Colbert as a colleague for over 10 years while I was employed at MIT as the Information Manager with MIT Sea Grant Program and as Communications Officer for The Research Laboratory of Electronics.  I witnessed her exemplary work as a graduate working on micro-sensors and then later, in addition to teaching advanced subjects,  developing, organizing, leading and evaluating STEM programs alternating summers.  My students enjoy her presentations for my bio-science program.","attribution":"Barbara Passero-MIT (Retired)"},{"quote":"Maru's work helps me raise awareness and funds.  Her readings set the tone for my film projects.  I am excited about the show planned for next Fall.  The proceeds will provide resources that help The Innocent Convicts fulfill its organizational mission-working to avoid wrongful convictions. Our collaborations and her continued oratorical, design, planning and production support have added complementary content to my events.  I and \"The Free 6\" applaud her commitment to social justice.","attribution":"Osagie Okoruwa-Filmmaker, The Innocent Convicts"},{"quote":"The 2020 Black History Month Celebration at St. Thomas' Episcopal Church was a standing-room-only joyful celebration of music and dance featuring artist of all ages.  The Lead Artistic Producer, Maru Colbert, directed talented artists (who) filled the hall with their exuberance and kept the audience in rapt attention. Her performance was amazing.  It has been a good while since I’ve heard such good music.  The event was a great success!","attribution":"Christina Manucy, Teresa Beall-Maryland"}]},"portfolio":[{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1614911984_944.jpg","title":"The Liberian Lab Project","desc":"Some of the micro-scale application and reaction-ware research I am doing benefits the Liberian Lab project.  Ultimately, I am seeking to re-establish the chemistry laboratory at the University of Liberia, which was decimated in that country's decade plus long civil war.","width":2988,"height":5312,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1546384136178,"order":1},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1546395825_796.jpg","title":"STEAM Trips for K-12","desc":"Through grant and volunteer programs students get out of school learning opportunities.  Science Nation Project School,  the National Society of Black Engineers, MIT K12 and BAMIT Alumni groups as well as other STEM groups contribute to this effort.","width":226,"height":135,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":2,"id":1546395825973},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959012_154.jpg","title":"My work...","desc":"During the past 35 years I have blended chemical, environmental and materials science engineering as well as  mathematics and urban design into a series of research and teaching projects.  My advanced and experiential learning courses incorporate this work and hopefully, are as motivational as they are educational.","width":1200,"height":1026,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1590959029441,"order":3},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959084_596.jpg","title":"I Am She...Black, With Faceted Edges...","desc":"This is the backdrop to one of the poems I wrote years ago.  Hopefully, I will find it soon.  This graphic reminds me to keep looking for it!  And \"RiRi\", you \"did that thang\", shining bright like a diamond during the 2023 Super Bowl half-time show!","width":650,"height":506,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1590959119935,"order":4},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959143_81.jpg","title":"Profile #1","desc":"This is one of a series of pictures that inspired my 15 minute choreopoem, \"A Collage of Woman\".  COVID-19 caused the cancellation of performances for a couple of years.  Maybe, finally, next year, for Women's History Month!","width":406,"height":500,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":5,"id":1590959143974},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959227_641.jpg","title":"....A Book","desc":"This is the inspiration for one of my unpublished works that I refer to each quarter.   One day I'll \"getter done\" as the expression goes!","width":172,"height":293,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":7,"id":1590959227763},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959254_321.jpg","title":"Engineering Art","desc":"When I develop STEAM exercises for my student groups I think of this graphic.  It is one of many I plan to put on a wall in one of my offices someday.","width":449,"height":263,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":8,"id":1590959255498},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959265_004.jpg","title":"The Word","desc":"This is \"my rock\"...my Bible, the source of my strength... the Living Word..\"The grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of our God endures forever.\"  Isaiah 40:8 NIV","width":225,"height":225,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":9,"id":1590959265129},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590959337_201.jpg","title":"There Is No Life Without Music....","desc":"\"Music, sweet music, you're the queen of my soul\"....Average White Band...I am so glad to resume my singing activities, especially performing a freedom opera written by a Black man in March 2023.","width":179,"height":282,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":10,"id":1590959337321},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1590964896_926.png","title":"On My Arm","desc":"I waited several years for Massachusetts to legalize tattoos.  Unlike some of my friends, I was not going to New York or New Hampshire-crossing state lines-to get one.  It's been years, however, due to fear I won't be getting it \"re-inked\" anytime soon!  Yes Aretha..\"A Rose Is Still A Rose\"...","width":674,"height":891,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":11,"id":1590964897077},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1592613808_66.png","title":"Cartoon Me!","desc":"This is meme \"me\" in many of the presentations I give all over the world.  Who needs a real picture when she has this great representation?  Thanks, whoever did this one!","width":540,"height":743,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":12,"id":1592613808874},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1592613999_597.gif","title":"\"Plume Science\"","desc":"This is a diagram from an engineering textbook I used in one of my most well-received courses.  I was teaching this online via Skype to international students on 4 continents long before COVID-19!","width":500,"height":264,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":13,"id":1592613999780},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1592614437_475.png","title":"Slam On It!","desc":"I received \"honorable mention\" in this one!","width":816,"height":1056,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":14,"id":1592614437642},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1592614516_652.jpg","title":"Math and More Math!","desc":"This is one of the professional societies I belong to.  The modeling I do relies on mathematics.  Success in engineering is predicated on mathematics.  And, after the Joint Mathematics Meetings I attended and now my SIAM/ICERM affiliation, I am reminded of how much MATH MATTERS!","width":2988,"height":5312,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":15,"id":1592614517120},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1592614622_43.jpg","title":"Boutique 4 Good","desc":"This is one of the items I designed for auctioning to raise money for my theater groups and this year, one of my professional chemistry organizations.  I normally make 1 for the auction and if asked by those who didn't have the winning bid, take custom orders for up to 5 more. ","width":5312,"height":2988,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":16,"id":1592614623111},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597155682_478.jpg","title":"Jacob Lawrence-The American Struggle/Panel I","desc":"After seeing this artist's \"Migration Series\" (and other works) I was once again, inspired. Although my graphic artistry is in fashion design and computer illustration, only, I am an art enthusiast and minor collector.  Given current issues, this painting resonated with me and motivated my future pairing of this and some of his other paintings for an interpretation of civil rights during Black History Month and daily.","width":2048,"height":1527,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1597156009517,"order":17},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597157473_44.jpg","title":"Royal Black Woman In Braids","desc":"My hair is, once again, in its usual, braided form. ","width":1600,"height":1689,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":18,"id":1597157473643},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597157967_6.jpg","title":"Black Woman Singing","desc":"...Finally, singing again, post-pandemic, to more than just walls and car windows.  Yes! to resumption of the Boston MFA concert this Winter, 2023!  Hopefully, there will be more singing soon..I miss the full choirs and the ensembles, leads and solos! \n","width":1600,"height":1499,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":19,"id":1597157967785},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597159504_413.jpg","title":"The Eye","desc":"Years ago, I wore burgundy contacts on occasion...Beauty IS in the \"eye of the beholder\" whatever the color!  Due to circumstances of late, I am finding wonder and \"the pretty\" everywhere....I have to, dwelling on the ugly is...ugly.","width":512,"height":480,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":20,"id":1597159504596},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597160122_014.jpg","title":"Jacob Lawrence-Tombstones","desc":"\"It's just too much\"..a line from \"For Colored Girls....\", a play I was in three times in two different roles.  Cancer, and/or (more recently) COVID, has claimed my mother, husband, mother-in-law, aunt, brother-in-law and friend's sister.  Sickle Cell Anemia took another friend.  A few others I've lost  to cancer are my renowned musician friend Gerri Allen and other luminaries such as Ron (of the Miracles), his daughter Michelle White (my young classmate), John Lewis and Aretha Franklin.","width":313,"height":437,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":21,"id":1597160122323},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597168179_284.gif","title":"Family Reunion Data","desc":"During our 1st virtual (56th annual) family reunion we played drawing, food, scavenger and other games.  Our graph of ages might have resembled this one.  We're missing some of the data from this August's 59th reunion. It was fun and I am so glad the reunion was in-person this year.  Planning for the 60th will begin shortly...in person again...yeah!","width":397,"height":235,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1597168371003,"order":22},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597168410_683.jpg","title":"Jacob-Lawrence-The Ballad of Margie Polite","desc":"On August 1, 1943, a rookie police officer accosted and arrested (Margie) after her alleged disorderly conduct in a Harlem hotel.  He shot Army Private Bandy who came to her aid.  News of the incident spread resulting in the two day Harlem 1943 Riot.  Langston Hughes and Jacob Lawrence marked the event with two poems (1943) and the painting (1948), respectively.  Adam Clayton Powell, Sr., said Bandy's actions were retaliation for White officers' brutality, without provocation, against Blacks. ","width":520,"height":758,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","order":23,"id":1597168410921},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597174564_638.jpg","title":"Elliptical Word Cloud-Social Justice","desc":"As is evident (everywhere) I am a social justice advocate-by necessity, I am living while Black...I am constantly engaged in my own form of protest.  I led a series on one of the outcomes of systemic bias against BIPOCs; over-representation of our men and women in the criminal justice system.  I wrote once, \"beaten until you're black and blue\" too often becomes \"Blue not beating until they see Black...\"  The next three items reflect my outreach.  One can march with more than the feet...","width":450,"height":313,"video_id":"","video_thumbnail":"","id":1597175621164,"order":24},{"type":"image","url":"https://assets.about.me/users/m/a/r/marucolbert_1597177522_223.png","title":"Engineering, Art and Criminal Justice","desc":"After hosting an interpretation of the Tufts University Art Gallery-Walls Turned Sideways-Artists Confront Justice System exhibition I am developing this first of three STE(A)M courses.  In conjunction with The Innocent Convicts, the National Society of Black Engineers, the Mass STEM Hub and my own Science Nation Project School students will complete this 12 week Geographical Information System mapping project.  It is based on a WTS exhibit wherein an artist compiled GIS maps of 5300 prisons. He started his first company – Solar Devices – in high school during the energy crisis of 1973 with a dream of making solar energy practical on a small scale. Sales of his solar plans and kits helped him pay his way through college at the California Institute of Technology.</p><p>While in college, Bill invented and patented a new high-performance loudspeaker design and started a company to manufacture those speakers called GNP Loudspeakers.</p><p>After Caltech, Bill created HAL the natural language interface for the Lotus 1-2-3 spreadsheet, which was at the time the leading software in the world. Bill’s company was acquired by Lotus, and while there he created many critically acclaimed software products.</p><p>In 1991, Bill started a new company called Knowledge Adventure, an educational software publisher that grew to be the third largest in the world. The company created the Jumpstart series of education products which revolutionized multimedia educational software. The company was acquired by Vivendi in 1995.</p><p>In 1996, filled with ideas, Bill decided to start his dream laboratory – a company “incubator” – modeled after Edison’s lab. Named Idealab, the company’s mission is to challenge the status quo, to be bold, and to tackle big ideas that others would not. During its more than two decades, it has started more than 150 companies, created more than 10,000 jobs, and had more than 45 successful IPOs and acquisitions.</p><p>Among the transformative changes that Bill has wrought is the invention of the business model that powers most of the monetization of the internet. Bill invented the “paid click”, or CPC (cost-per-click) model with the company GoTo.com/Overture, which he founded in 1998. After a successful IPO the company was acquired by Yahoo in 2003 for $1.6 billion. Today, Bill’s pioneering idea is the backbone of internet monetization and remains one of his most significantly impactful inventions.</p><p>In addition to serving as Idealab’s chairman, Bill is also The dedication and sacrifices made by her parents to give her and her siblings a better life instilled her with a strong work ethic that she carries with her to this day. Growing up as an undocumented youth in Crown Heights, she faced many obstacles and challenges. Those experiences give her insight into the shared experience across immigrant communities who came to the United States to pursue the American Dream and the experiences of all those striving to succeed in the face of setbacks. Her ability to overcome these obstacles, with the support that she received from her community, laid the foundation for her passion for public service and supporting those that are most vulnerable in our society.</p><p>With 15 years of experience in the government, strategic partnerships and community relations, Sarana has contributed to the work of various levels of government. She has served as the Director of Constituent Services, District Office Manager and Office Administrator in the New York State Assembly in the 43rd District and she has served as the Deputy Chief of Staff in both the City Council and New York State Senate offices, Office of the Brooklyn Borough President and most recently the Office of the Mayor. Her time in government has allowed her to work and lead on initiatives around public safety, lead testing programs and accessibility for the residents of NYCHA and organizing with tenants to help keep them in their homes.</p><p>Volunteerism has always played a vital role throughout Sarana’s life. Upon completing her studies at CUNY’s Lehman College, in 2008 she volunteered with CUNY Citizenship. In more recent years, Sarana has served as a Board Member of Life of Hope, a community-based organization which supports immigrants, youth and families in Central Brooklyn, where she taught citizenship and naturalization courses and organized workshops on immigrants’ rights, assisting others seeking their American Dream.</p><p>She is a firm champion of building partnership between government institutions, community-based organizations, clergy, small businesses, and other stakeholders, as she knows firsthand the profound impact coalition building has on improving underserved communities and enhancing quality of life.</p><p>As a community leader, organizer and a mom, Sarana is dedicated to ensuring pathways to opportunity is accessible to all people.</p>","contact_me":{"enabled":true,"display":"form"},"tags":[],"interests":[{"interest":"Politics"},{"interest":"Volunteering"},{"interest":"Innovation"},{"interest":"Causes"}],"locations":[{"source":"user","location":"Brooklyn, NY","components":[]}],"schools":[{"school":"Lehman College CUNY"}],"jobs":[{"job":"Public Servant "}],"roles":[{"role":"Coalition Builder"},{"role":"Community Organizer"},{"role":"Collaborator"}],"video":{"type":"youtube","url":"https://youtu.be/iYtcysi2cTw","video_id":"iYtcysi2cTw","video_thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iYtcysi2cTw/maxresdefault.jpg"},"testimonials":{"header":"2","items":[{"quote":"Sarana Purcell has over 15 years of experience in government, and has been instrumental in many progressive initiatives that have provided services and access to resources to New Yorkers, especially those within the 43rd Assembly District. Mike and the team help millions of couples navigate and enjoy life's biggest moments together through industry-leading digital and media products that include The Knot, The Bump, The Nest, and Gigmasters. In his career, Mike has helped to launch or scale over a dozen innovative businesses, generating more than one billion dollars in new revenue across digital marketplaces, media, local, mobile, video, ad tech, and ecommerce.</p><p>Mike joined XO Group as president in July 2013 and assumed the CEO role in March 2014. During Mike’s tenure, XO Group has transformed from a traditional online media company to a digital marketplace that connects young couples to the event professionals, services, and products that they need to successfully get married and become parents.</p><p>Mike serves on the board of Fortune 500 financial services company, Ally Financial (NYSE: ALLY), and is Co-chairman of the Board of Literacy Partners, a nonprofit that has provided family support services to thousands of New Yorkers for over forty years.</p><p>From 2011 to 2013, Mike served as CEO of Vente-Privee USA, an ecommerce venture backed by American Express. Previously, Mike spent 4 ½ years at Google helping to build Google’s mobile and video advertising businesses. Before Google, Mike was the General Manager of Strategic Ventures at NBC Universal, where he received the GE Imagination Breakthrough award. Mike earlier served as vice president in the NBC Corporate Development group. Mike worked previously at Walker Digital, an internet incubator, and at McKinsey &amp; Company.</p><p>Mike has been recognized as one of Crain’s New York \"40 Under 40,\" Multichannel News “40 Under 40,” Folio's \"100\" honorees, TV Week's \"Twelve to Watch,\" TV Week's “Hot List,” and has received a CEO World Award and a Stevie International Business Award.</p><p>Mike has appeared on NBC's Today show, CNBC, Bloomberg, and Fox Business, as well as in The New York Times, Wall Street Journal, Fortune, Entrepreneur, TechCrunch, Fast Company, NY Post, AdAge, AdWeek, Newsday, and others.</p><p>Mike received a BA in Economics and a BA in International Relations from the University of Pennsylvania. He is a named inventor of three digital media patents and played a supporting actor role in the independent film The Mad Ones. Throughout my career I've worked as an anchor, host, reporter, photographer, editor and web producer. Before all that stuff, I drove 18 wheelers. Yup, 18 wheelers!!! More about that in just a second.</p>
<p>Currently, I'm a news anchor and host for KDKA -TV in Pittsburgh. I anchor the weekday editions of KDKA TV News at Noon and 4. I also host <em>'Your Pittsburgh'</em> a show dedicated to what's new and positive in The Burgh.</p>
<p>Before moving to Pittsburgh, I worked in Cleveland (yes, I own both Browns and Steelers jerseys) for ABC affiliate WEWS Newschannel 5. There, I anchored Good Morning Cleveland Monday- Friday. I also developed a weekly franchise called '<em>Terrific Teacher Tribute.'</em> Each week, I recognized a Northeast Ohio teacher who excels in the classroom. I took tremendous pride in this segment. I did everything myself including the writing, the camera work, editing and uploading of the information and finished video product to the station’s web site. It was good stuff if I do say so myself.</p>
<p>I got my start in TV in my home state of South Carolina working for CBS affiliate WBTW News 13 in the Florence/Myrtle Beach market. While there, I solo anchored three hours of morning weekday news and produced and anchored News 13 at Noon.</p>
<p>I have volunteered my time to numerous charitable and civic organizations over the years including the Junior League of Cleveland and Pittsburgh. I've served on a lot of boards too -- just too many to list here.</p>
<p>I emcee a lot of events in the community. I especially enjoy talking to young kids about how to turn dreams into SMART goals -and make them come true.</p>
<p>I've been fortunate enough to be recognized in newspapers and magazines for my work in front of the camera and in the community. The Ohio Broadcaster’s Hall of Fame named me its Personality of the Year for 2009. I'm also a two time Emmy award winner.</p>
<p>I have a Journalism degree from The University of South Carolina. I also hold a Master’s degree in Business from Ashland University, Ashland, OH</p>
<p>Now, back to that truck driving thing. I paid my way through college by driving 18-wheelers for FedEx. On the weekends I fueled airplanes for Eagle Aviation. One day, I'd like to learn to fly.</p>
<p>In case you're wondering, I ALWAYS keep my Class A commercial truck driver's license current - just in case this TV gig doesn't work out</p>","contact_me":{"enabled":false,"display":"form"},"tags":[],"interests":[{"interest":"Photography"},{"interest":"Cooking"},{"interest":"Football"},{"interest":"Music"},{"interest":"Food"}],"locations":[{"source":"google_string","location":"Detroit, Michigan, USA","components":[]}],"schools":[{"school":"University of South Carolina"}],"jobs":[{"job":"WDIV- TV"}],"roles":[{"role":"News Anchor"}],"twitter_username":"kimberlygill","portfolio":[],"apps":[{"id":13,"platform":"favs","display_order":0},{"id":22,"platform":"linkedin","display_order":0,"site_url":"http://www.linkedin.com/in/kimberlygill"},{"id":21,"platform":"youtube","display_order":1,"site_url":"http://www.youtube.com/user/kimberlydgill"},{"id":1,"platform":"twitter","display_order":2,"site_url":"https://www.twitter.com/kimberlygill"},{"id":3,"platform":"foursquare","display_order":3,"site_url":"http://www.foursquare.com/user/604664"},{"id":20,"platform":"instagram","display_order":5,"site_url":"http://instagram.com/kimberlygilltv"},{"id":23,"platform":"flickr","display_order":6,"site_url":"http://www.flickr.com/people/kimberlygill/"}],"actions":{},"spotlight":{"type":"watch_video","text":"","url":"http://youtube.com/kimberlydgill"},"settings":{},"layout":{"version":1,"template_id":"large","color_theme_id":null,"color":"6C45C4"},"images":[{"active":true,"height":1050,"url":"https://assets.about.me/background/users/k/i/m/kimberlygill_1403132205_06.jpg","width":701,"id":"kimberlygill_1403132205_06","timestamp":1553810592668,"highlight":{"x":189.25016699975197,"y":393.85211181640625,"w":350.5,"h":350.4958190917969}}],"mapped_domains":[],"allowed_features":[]}},"viewer":{"anonymous":true},"analytics":{"trackingId":"G-LE3EMX7RDC"}}</script>

<p>I moved to New York after falling in love with the people and energy of the city and through numerous guest DJ appearances. New York City has been my home for over 15 years now.</p>
<p>I started a residency at a club called Liquids in the East Village.This residency allowed me to express my diverse taste in music. My style attracted the interest of many people in the music industry.I went on to guest DJ in many of New York’s top clubs as well as performing at diverse venues such as The World Trade Center, Brooklyn Academy of Music, Grand Central Station amongst others.</p>
<p>I set up an events planning company called Juggernaut, that invited some of the best DJ’s and producers from around the world to perform .My events invited artists such as Groove Armada, Grandmaster Flash, Giles Peterson,Derrick May, Kelis, Timo Maas , David Morales and Adam Freeland to name but a few.</p>
<p>I have hosted events for various Fashion designers and Model Agencies as well as Corporate clients,including parties hosted and attended by Bruce Willis, Christy Turlington,Mario Testino, U2 and The Red Hot Chili Peppers.</p>
<p>I opened “Le Royale” in the West Village,New York. acts and DJ’s that performed during its existence Included Lady GaGa, and Guns and Roses,Justice, Kid Cudi, Peter Bjorn and John,Crystal Castles,Diplo,Dragonettes,Steve Aoki and many more. This was truly a nightclub that revolutionized the electro, rock, dance and house movement.</p>","contact_me":{"enabled":false,"display":"form"},"tags":[],"interests":[],"locations":[{"location":"New York","source":"tokenbox"}],"schools":[],"jobs":[],"roles":[],"portfolio":[],"apps":[],"actions":{},"settings":{},"layout":{"version":1,"template_id":"medium","color_theme_id":null,"color":"F76B1D"},"images":[{"active":true,"height":720,"thumbnail_url":"https://assets.about.me/thumbnail/users/t/e/r/terrycasey_1363795159_24.jpg","url":"https://assets.about.me/background/users/t/e/r/terrycasey_1363795159_24.jpg","width":960,"id":"terrycasey_1363795159_24"}],"mapped_domains":[],"allowed_features":[]}},"viewer":{"anonymous":true},"analytics":{"trackingId":"G-LE3EMX7RDC"}}</script>

It's a peculiarity of this country that the inquisitive are too polite to hazard a guess. Perhaps they've made the mistake before of suggesting to a Scotsman that he may be English. The backlash from that would be enough to knock the confidence of anyone, except perhaps a Scotsman.</p><p>And so my answer of \"I was born in Yugoslavia but I grew up in England\" has been honed over the years to ease into the rest of the conversation as kindly as possible. Patting themselves on the back for picking up that I wasn't entirely English, people set free their curiosity to discover that I came to live in Denver in 1996 (by way of Australia) where I met my wife before following her to New York in November 2001, marrying her a year later in Slovenia (a country which does still exist), and that I help people make maps that help improve the world.</p><p>Of late, most of these conversations take place at the dog run. You see, without any particular interest in cultivating and growing our own children, we adopted a dog, which has proven to be more life-changing than I had anticipated. I've primarily worked from home since I moved to New York, and so I had never got a real sense of living in a neighbourhood: I never walked through one to work and if I went out it was to go and work elsewhere. But a dog forces you outside with nothing better to do than just walk, and be, and in my case notice at last that the East Village truly is a village. It feels like home to me now. I'm greeted in the street not with offers of narcotics in exchange for cash, but with smiles and recognition. It is truly rewarding.</p><p>Lastly, my middle name is Igor.</p>","contact_me":{"enabled":false,"display":"form"},"tags":[],"interests":[{"interest":"Maps"},{"interest":"Dogs"},{"interest":"Technology"}],"locations":[{"components":[{"long_name":"New York","types":["locality","political"]},{"short_name":"NY","long_name":"New York","types":["administrative_area_level_1","political"]},{"short_name":"US","long_name":"United States","types":["country","political"]}],"source":"google","location":"New York, NY, United States"}],"schools":[],"jobs":[],"roles":[{"role":"Software Engineer"},{"role":"East Village Policeman"}],"twitter_username":"nixta","portfolio":[],"apps":[{"id":1,"platform":"twitter","display_order":1,"site_url":"https://www.twitter.com/nixta"},{"id":2,"platform":"facebook","display_order":1,"site_url":"http://www.facebook.com/nixta"},{"id":4,"platform":"linkedin","display_order":1,"site_url":"http://www.linkedin.com/in/nixta"},{"id":5,"platform":"tumblr","display_order":1,"site_url":"http://nixta.tumblr.com"},{"id":6,"platform":"flickr","display_order":1,"site_url":"http://www.flickr.com/people/flixta/"},{"id":7,"platform":"github","display_order":6,"site_url":"https://github.com/nixta"}],"actions":{},"spotlight":{"type":"visit_site","text":"Visit my website","url":"http://nixtarolls.nixta.com"},"settings":{},"layout":{"version":1,"template_id":"small","color_theme_id":null,"color":"305B90"},"images":[{"active":true,"width":636,"height":636,"source":"upload","url":"https://assets.about.me/background/users/n/i/x/nixta_nixta.com_1477518542_48.jpg","timestamp":1477518543641,"highlight":{"y":170.66,"x":159,"w":318,"h":318},"id":"02fcca50-9bc6-11e6-81a8-2bdc60879bd4"}],"mapped_domains":[],"allowed_features":[]}},"viewer":{"anonymous":true},"analytics":{"trackingId":"G-LE3EMX7RDC"}}</script>
